We state the following in our [JIRA workflow doc|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Configuring+Workflow#ConfiguringWorkflow-Using%27commontransitions%27]:

{quote}"Copy the default workflow — the default workflow contains common transitions. Although you cannot edit the default workflow, you can copy it and then edit its steps and transitions to suit your requirements."{quote}

This doesn't appear to be completely accurate. You can clone the default workflow, which does copy its common transitions, however you cannot do anything meaningful with those common transitions --- like rename them or add them to other steps, without editing the workflow in XML. We should make this clear.

